<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-09-26T16:21:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-09-26T16:21:00-05:00" n="815" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d815">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/5285: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Commissioner at Helsingfors</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Haynes</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Helsingfors</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-26T23:00:00+01:39"><hi rend="italic">September 26,
                                        1919, 11 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received September 27, 9:08
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>435. It is certain Esthonia and Latvia will conclude peace with the
                            Bolsheviki. Lithuania and Finland unlikely but Finland may if the
                            Socialists succeed in their efforts to have Diet called to decide the
                            matter.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Haynes</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>